      "type": "eq",
      "start": 46,
      "end": 62,
      "html": "<section class=\"slide eq\"><ul class=\"eq-lines\"><li id=\"imp89sfoo13\" class=\" eq-item eq-title \" > General Identity Pattern </li><li id=\"imp89sfoo14\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ (x+y)^2=x^2+2xy+y^2 $$ </li><li id=\"imp89sfoo15\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > The middle term always doubles. </li><li id=\"imp89sfoo16\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > Careless expansion causes mistakes. </li><li id=\"imp89sfoo17\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > Stepwise reasoning prevents confusion. </li></ul><div class=\"eq-side-panel\"><div id=\"imp89sfoo13-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"eq.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imp89sfoo13-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Variables can change without changing structure. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo13-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Only the symbols are different. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo13-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > (x+y)^2 </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo13-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The reasoning process stays identical. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo14-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"box.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imp89sfoo14-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > This is the standard algebraic identity. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo14-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > It appears repeatedly in mathematics. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo14-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Students should memorize the structure. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo14-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > middle\\ term=2xy </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo15-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"image.png\" /></div><div id=\"imp89sfoo15-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Two identical cross products appear. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo15-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > xy+xy=2xy </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo15-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > This pattern is consistent. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo15-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The coefficient becomes 2. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo16-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"force-intro.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imp89sfoo16-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Missing one product changes the answer. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo16-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Students often forget the second middle term. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo16-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > xy\\neq2xy </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo16-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Write every multiplication explicitly. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo17-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"eq.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imp89sfoo17-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Clear structure improves understanding. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo17-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Each step preserves context. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo17-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Visual pacing supports memory. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoo17-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Students can follow calmly. </div></div></section>",
